Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put the @chicken stock powder{1%pot} and @water for the stock{750%ml}(for the stock) in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Bring to a simmer. Stir to dissolve the stock pot, then reduce the heat to low. Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into ½cm pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Thinly slice the @shiitake mushrooms{50%g} and @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}(sliced).

Twist and tear the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} in half then roughly chop. Zest the lemon. Lay a slice of @serrano ham{2%slices} lengthways on a #chopping board{}. Place the @British chicken breasts{2} horizontally across the middle of the ham. Wrap the ham around the chicken to enclose it. Place them seam-side down on a lightly oiled #baking tray{}. Repeat with the remaining chicken and ham. Roast the chicken on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put a glug of @olive oil{2%tbsp} in another large, wide-bottomed saucepan on medium heat. Add the shallot and mushrooms. Cook, stirring, until the shallot is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the @Arborio rice{175%g} and stir, making sure the rice is coated, cook for ~{1%minute}. Add a ladleful of the stock and stir. Once the rice has absorbed the stock, add another ladleful and repeat.

Continue adding ladlefuls of stock, stirring regularly until it has all been absorbed by the rice. This should take ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Let the rice absorb each ladleful of stock before adding the next.

In between stints of stirring, put the @lemon oil{for drizzling} in a #small bowl{} and add the lemon zest and parsley.

When the chicken is cooked through, remove from your oven and leave to rest on the baking tray, covered in some #foil{}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

> If you've run out of stock before the risotto is cooked, just add a splash of water and keep cooking.

When the risotto is ready, add the @unsalted butter{15%g} and @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and beat vigorously. Taste and add some @salt{} and @black pepper{} if you like.

Cut each chicken breast into six slices. Spoon the risotto into deep #bowls{} and top with the @wild rocket{40%g} leaves. Sit the chicken on top of the rocket and finish with a drizzle of the lemon and parsley oil.

> Buon appetito!